-- Ghana's Economy Revalued to Be 75% Bigger Than Earlier Thought in 2010
-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 2010-11-05T10:46:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-05/ghana-s-economy-revalued-to-be-75-bigger-than-earlier-thought-in-2010.html
Ghana’s gross domestic product has
been revalued at 44.8 billion cedis ($31.2 billion) for 2010, 75
percent higher than an earlier estimate of 25.6 billion cedis,
according to the Ghana Statistical Service.  The new figures are based on a reassesment of the size and
value of the West African nation’s economy, Grace Bediako, head
of the Accra-based agency, told reporters today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Moses Mozart Dzawu in Accra at 
 mdzawu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
